    • Method Detail

      • viewDetails

        void viewDetails(org.w3c.dom.Element outputElement)
        The output element contains the output xml for the getExceptionList api call. getExceptionList is called to get two types of alerts. a) new alerts b) follow up alerts The output xml obtained from both the api calls are provided in the output element. When the user clicks on the link provided on the alert pop up. This methos will be invoked. For eg. One can use this method to show details of the alerts assigned by processing the output element. A sample output element template will look like this: 
                <InboxList>
                <Inbox Description="" DetailDescription="" ExceptionType=""  InboxKey="" InboxType="" Priority="" />
        </InboxList>
        Parameters:
        outputElement -

      • getExceptionListForAlertNotification

        org.w3c.dom.Document getExceptionListForAlertNotification(long lastPolledTime)
        This method is used to get the input xml for calling api getExceptionList for getting the new alerts assigned to user. getExceptionList is called to get two types of alerts. a) new alerts b) follow up alerts The input xml returned by this method is used to get the new alerts assigned to user. Return null if default api call has to be made, for making customized calls one has to provide the input xml required to make the api call. For example the default api call returns alerts of all priority, if one needs to show only alerts of priority one, then the input xml required to call the api should be returned in this method The default input xml template used for getting new alerts 
          
        <Inbox Status="CLOSED" StatusQryType="NE" SubscribedQueues="">
         <User Loginid=""/>
                <InboxAuditList> 
                <InboxAudit CreatetsQryType="" ToUserKey=""/>
                </InboxAuditList>
        </Inbox>
        Parameters:
        lastPolledTime -
        Returns:
        Note:The vale of the attribute Createts will be set by the platform.If overriding this attribute be careful.

      • getExceptionListForFollowupAlert

        org.w3c.dom.Document getExceptionListForFollowupAlert(long lastPolledTime)
        This method is used to get the input xml for calling api getExceptionList for getting the follow up alerts. getExceptionList is called to get two types of alerts. a) new alerts: The new alerts assigned to user. b) follow up alerts: The follow up alerts The input xml returned by this method is used to get the the followup alerts assigned to user. Return null if default api call has to be made, for making customized calls one has to provide the input xml required to make the api call. For example the default api call returns alerts of all priority, if one needs to show only alerts of priority one, then the input xml required to call the api should be returned in this method The default input xml template used for getting follow up alerts 
           
        <Inbox FollowupDateQryType="" FromFollowupDate="" Status="" StatusQryType="" ToFollowupDate="">
                <User Loginid=""/>
        </Inbox>
        Parameters:
        lastPolledTime -
        Returns:

      • isFollowUpAlertNotificationRequired

        boolean isFollowUpAlertNotificationRequired()
        This method is used to disable follow up alerts api call.
        Returns:
        true if follow up alert needs to be shown. NOTE:Follow up alerts are shown on alert pop up only if there are no new alerts created.
